Someone came to repair the floor of my kitchen, so I'll just pretend I still have a job and work from home while reviewing Too Hot to Handle.
If I can only open this accursed file. (Damn OneDrive.)
*pirate voice* I'm in.
And that's where it starts to drill really hard. Great!
His passive-aggressive way of turning my air purifier to max makes me uncomfortable, but it smells like wood shavings, so it's justified even if it's an anti-mask. And besides, I really need to protect myself, don't I?
I really want to go back to bed, but I can't until he's gone.
The positive point is that I've finished re-reading chapter 4!
Chapter five is long, but big suspense. Good work.
Busy replacing... ➡️ ellipsis character, and there are 54 in this chapter 😅
But good, I care. The most natural-talking sentences are mostly chopped up, especially when people let themselves go with their emotions.
The craftsman is sweeping with a bit of luck, he'll soon be finished.
He went out (from what I hear) to cut something. So I took a look to see where he was at. It's far from finished :(
More than 7 pages left on chapter five. It's still my favorite chapter, and it's pretty much done. A few minor layout changes, and some minor changes to switch to the active voice and improve concision. Although, I could really use a break and a cup of tea, but the guy is still fiddling around in my kitchen.
He just started sweeping again. I hope that's a good sign.
The craftsman is gone!
He told me he had prepared an estimate for the whole floor, but the owners were stingy and paid only for the small damaged area near the door. It's definitely better.
The house is airing out, and my air purifier is running in the kitchen while I'm enjoying a cup of tea in the garden!
